{"lemma":"ذَقْنٌ","slug":"ذَقْنٌ","root":"ذ.ق.ن","root_slug":"ذ-ق-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ذ-ق-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n13911","n13912","n13913"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B0%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"chin"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"beard on the chin; goatee","tags":["Arabic","Modern","Standard","broadly"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"beard on the chin; goatee; beard","tags":["Arabic","Modern","Standard","broadly","dialectal","proscribed"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From ذ ق ن (ḏ q n), from Proto-Semitic *ḏaḳan- (“beard”). Compare Hebrew זָקָן (zāqān) and Ugaritic 𐎄𐎖𐎐 (dqn)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13911","headword_ar":"ذِقْنٌ","root":"*qn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"decrepit, old and weak, or extremely aged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"man. (K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n13912","headword_ar":"ذَقَنٌ","root":"*qn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chin;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place where the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laHoyaAnN","text_ar":"لَحْيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two lateral portions of the lower jaw"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"combine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at their lower part:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) it is of a man (S, Msb) [and of a beast]: also pronounced with kesr (ISd, K) to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*","text_ar":"ذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iqanN","text_ar":"ذِقَنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TK:) of the masc. gender, (Lh, K,) only: (Lh, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*oqaAnN","text_ar":"اَذْقَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":968},{"kind":"text","text":"a pl. of pauc.; and the pl. of mult. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uquwnN","text_ar":"ذُقُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) Hence, (K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muvoqalN A@sotaEaAna bi*aqanihi","text_ar":"مُثْقَلٌ ا@سْتَعَانَ بِذَقَنِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A heavily-burdened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overburdened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sought to help himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"to rise"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of his chin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, M, K:) a prov., applied to a low, base, or mean, and weak man, who seeks to help himself by means of another man like himself; (S;) or to him who seeks to help himself by means of one who has no power of defending, and by means of one more low, base, or mean, and weak, than he: (M:) or to him who seeks to help himself by means of one less than he: (K:) originating from the fact that a camel laden with a heavy load, and unable to rise, bears with his chin upon the ground. (S, K.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xir~uwA liA^a*oqaAnihimo","text_ar":"خِرُّوا لِاَذْقَانِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They fell down prostrate, with their chins to the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see the Kur xvii. 108 and 109]: and [hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSafato riyHN faxar~ati AlA^a$ojaAru","text_ar":"عَصَفَتْ رِيحٌ فَخَرَّتِ الاَشْجَارُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liloA^a*oqaAni","text_ar":"لِلْاَذْقَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wind blew violently, so that the trees fell,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bent themselves down to the ground"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xr","text_ar":"خر"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hab~ti Alr~iyHu fakab~ati Al$~ajara EalaY","text_ar":"هَبّتِ الرِّيحُ فَكَبَّتِ الشَّجَرَ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*oqaAnihaA","text_ar":"اَذْقَانِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wind blew, and overturned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"threw down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bent down, the trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and, of a stone,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kab~ahu Als~ayolu li*aqanihi","text_ar":"كَبَّهُ السَّيْلُ لِذَقَنِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The torrent overturned it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair that grows upon the chin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"used in this sense by the vulgar; and said by Esh-Shiháb El-Khafajee, in the “ Shifá el-Ghaleel, ” to be post-classical: Z says, in the “ Rabeea el-Abrár, ” that it signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beard"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the language of the Nabathæans. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","S","Msb","K","ISd","TK","Lh","TA","M"]},{"entry_id":"n13913","headword_ar":"ذِقَنٌ","root":"*qn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph, first sentence."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}